### Notes

*   ^ Due to the division of Germany, Konrad Adenauer served as Chancellor of West Germany, not of a unified Germany. The term "West Germany" is the common English designation for the Federal Republic of Germany during the period from its formation on 23 May 1949, until German reunification on 3 October 1990, when [East Germany](/East_Germany) acceded.
*   ^ Pronunciation: [/ˈædənaʊər, ˈɑːd-/](/Help:IPA/English) A(H)D-ən-our; German: [ˈkɔnʁaːt ˈhɛʁman ˈjoːzɛf ˈʔaːdənaʊɐ](/Help:IPA/Standard_German) [ⓘ](/File:De-Konrad_Hermann_Joseph_Adenauer.ogg).
*   ^ During his final overseas trip in February 1967, Adenauer met with General Franco. As a lifelong art enthusiast, he seized the opportunity to visit the Prado Museum. His last major address, delivered at Madrid's Ateneo Palace, concluded with an exhortation to continue the ongoing process of European unification.
*   ^ [Beji Caid Essebsi](/Beji_Caid_Essebsi), President of Tunisia (2014–2019), was between 88 and 92 years old during his term. Malaysian Prime Minister [Mahathir Mohamad](/Mahathir_Mohamad) (2018–2020) served from ages 92 to 94. Italian President [Giorgio Napolitano](/Giorgio_Napolitano), who turned 88 in 2013 and remained in office until 2015 at age 89, held a largely ceremonial role and did not direct the government of Italy.
*   ^ The 10,000 returnees comprised Wehrmacht personnel and civilians convicted of war crimes by Soviet Military Tribunals. Among those repatriated in 1955 were Luftwaffe fighter ace [Erich Hartmann](/Erich_Hartmann), Generals Leopold von Babenhausen and [Friedrich Foertsch](/Friedrich_Foertsch), [Walther von Seydlitz-Kurzbach](/Walther_von_Seydlitz-Kurzbach), and Hitler's personal pilot [Hans Baur](/Hans_Baur).

